1
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:54,888
Coming.

2
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:58,224
That wasn't the first time

3
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,729
that my life was turned upside down.

4
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:09,569
Who are you?

5
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,620
I learned that

6
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:21,456
one day is all it takes

7
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:24,959
for my entire life

8
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:29,172
to be turned upside down.

9
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:32,342
I learned that…

10
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:33,968
Hi.

11
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:35,512
Long time no see.

12
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:38,932
…for the first time 20 years ago.

13
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:41,017
ON DUTY FOR YOUR SAFETY AND HAPPINESS
YOUNGSAN POLICE STATION

14
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:45,271
Hey, kid.

15
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,315
Is something wrong?

16
00:01:47,816 --> 00:01:48,775
Do you need help?

17
00:01:54,322 --> 00:01:55,740
Wait, is that…

18
00:01:55,824 --> 00:01:57,200
blood on your clothes?

19
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:05,083
Hey!

20
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:09,379
YOUNGSAN EXPRESS BUS TERMINAL

21
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:20,223
LEGAL NAME CHANGE FORM

22
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:21,307
And

23
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:23,184
I heard…

24
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:26,479
NEW NAME
KIM HYE-JOO

25
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:28,189
…that name again…

26
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:29,566
Kim Jae-eun.

27
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:34,571
…for the first time in 20 years.

28
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:36,614
Or should I say…

29
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:38,199
Kim Hye-joo?

30
00:02:45,081 --> 00:02:46,249
You murderer.

31
00:02:58,761 --> 00:03:00,722
CONFRONTATION

32
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:03,641
How have you been?

33
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:06,436
Right.

34
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,605
I know it's late,
but congratulations on your marriage.

35
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:11,399
The wife of an assemblyman?

36
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:13,276
That's amazing.

37
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:24,329
You had reached out to my chief advisor

38
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:27,415
but I wanted to meet you personally.

39
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:33,838
Look…

40
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:35,256
Is that your daughter?

41
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:36,466
No.

42
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:38,384
Then who is she?

43
00:03:42,388 --> 00:03:43,348
She's a kid I know.

44
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:51,314
Yes, she's just a kid I know.

45
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:54,317
Look, Seung-hee.

46
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:58,154
I'm a bit busy today,

47
00:03:58,696 --> 00:03:59,697
so let's talk…

48
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,283
Let's talk another time, okay?

49
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:06,996
All right.

50
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:10,250
Let me get your number then.

51
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:12,001
Sure.

52
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:30,979
Save my number.

53
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:32,772
I'll call you.

54
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,776
Okay.

55
00:04:39,153 --> 00:04:40,571
It's so nice to see you.

56
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,328
I missed you,

57
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:49,330
my friend.

58
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,377
See you later.

59
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:07,015
Ms. Kim.

60
00:05:08,516 --> 00:05:09,350
Ms. Kim.

61
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:17,358
Let's visit Ji-hoon some other time.

62
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:20,528
I'm feeling unwell.
I need to get some rest.

63
00:05:30,496 --> 00:05:31,331
What?

64
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:32,248
My name?

65
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,333
Yes.

66
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,169
I'm taking out a mortgage
to fund the election campaign.

67
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,212
I needed our resident registration forms

68
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,214
since the house
is under both of our names,

69
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:42,300
and yours said you had changed your name.

70
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:43,760
Kim Jae-eun?

71
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:46,596
It's a pretty name. Why did you change it?

72
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:50,266
No reason.

73
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:52,685
"Kim Jae-eun."

74
00:05:53,936 --> 00:05:55,188
That's new.

75
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:57,148
Go to bed first.

76
00:05:57,732 --> 00:05:58,941
I'll be in the study.

77
00:06:16,584 --> 00:06:18,711
Thank you for reaching out to us.

78
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:25,009
I came here to tell you
to stop what you're doing.

79
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:28,513
My mother-in-law has done nothing wrong.

80
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:31,599
We can get into that later.

81
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,310
Are you originally from Youngsan?

82
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,729
It's also my wife's hometown.

83
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,107
I see.

84
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:44,779
She often talks about
fond memories of Youngsan,

85
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:48,866
so whenever I meet people from there,
I feel at home as well.

86
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:52,495
But I try to stay professional

87
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,038
and distinguish

88
00:06:54,872 --> 00:06:56,165
right from wrong.

89
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:13,266
Now that we're acquainted,
try to arrange a meal with him.

90
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:16,811
What are you doing?

91
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:20,773
Sir, it's about Ji Seung-kyu's family.

92
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:22,692
Ji Seung…

93
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:24,610
Right, the medical student? What is it?

94
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,948
His mother swallowed some pills.

95
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:41,002
Do you think Mr. Nam's meeting
with Mr. Choi didn't go very well?

96
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:43,212
He's been looking kind of uneasy.

97
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:44,839
Right?

98
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:47,175
What could it be?

99
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,219
ASSEMBLYMAN'S OFFICE

100
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:51,637
Thanks. Bye.

101
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:59,270
They pumped her stomach,
so her life is not in danger.

102
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:04,150
Why did she do it?

103
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:07,403
I'm not sure.

104
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:08,321
Well…

105
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,991
She must be either heartbroken
over the loss of her son

106
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:13,701
or shocked by the hateful comments.

107
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:18,789
Every article about him had quite a few
comments saying that he deserved to die.

108
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:24,962
I called them "hateful comments",

109
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,340
but that's the public sentiment.

110
00:08:28,090 --> 00:08:30,092
So please don't blame yourself

111
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:32,970
for what happened to him or his mother.

112
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,688
Are you thinking about Ji-hoon?

113
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:47,026
How could I not?

114
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:50,863
He must have received
tens of thousands of hate comments.

115
00:08:51,614 --> 00:08:53,324
Every time he did something wrong

116
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:55,743
and even after his death.

117
00:08:57,954 --> 00:08:59,997
It's true that what he did was wrong,

118
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:03,668
and he should be scolded
and punished for it.

119
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:08,005
But…

120
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,675
NAM JOONG-DO MUST TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR HIS SON'S MISDEEDS AND STEP DOWN

121
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,220
Most parents beg for mercy

122
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:18,015
when their children do something wrong…

123
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:21,394
I ask for him to be punished
strictly by the law,

124
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:24,355
and I sincerely apologize as his father

125
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:26,774
for failing to discipline him properly.

126
00:09:26,857 --> 00:09:28,276
THE NATIONAL ASSEMBLY
OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA

127
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,445
…but I did the opposite.

128
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:34,031
Hi, honey.

129
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:46,544
NAM APOLOGIZES FOR SON'S ASSAULT CASE
AT PRESS CONFERENCE

130
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,883
And it hurt my wife greatly.

131
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:00,141
Don't give a criminal a narrative.

132
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:04,812
What?

133
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,482
"Don't give a criminal a narrative."

134
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:11,444
That's what the audience says these days

135
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:15,239
when characters in movies or dramas
say something like that.

136
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:19,327
They refuse to give criminals
any room for pity

137
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,078
or being understood.

138
00:10:21,704 --> 00:10:23,164
That's the public sentiment.

139
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:28,210
I have a heavy heart
whenever I think of Ji-hoon,

140
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,463
but that's the reality.

141
00:10:32,506 --> 00:10:34,383
What I mean by that is,

142
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:37,428
you have to keep your pity,
or any form of personal sentiments

143
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:40,056
toward Ji-hoon or
Ji Seung-kyu's mother, at home.

144
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:42,516
You should only express it to your wife.

145
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:45,978
You're not Ji-hoon's father right now.

146
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:48,272
You're an assemblyman
with an election coming up.

147
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:51,192
Just like you said,
you have to stay professional.

148
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:16,801
If you were to lose your child,

149
00:11:17,718 --> 00:11:19,804
what would you rather have
the cause of death be?

150
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:23,182
Suicide, murder…

151
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:26,268
or an accident?

152
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,441
The last one would be the least painful.

153
00:11:38,447 --> 00:11:39,990
It would be, wouldn't it?

154
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:41,826
Yes.

155
00:11:44,912 --> 00:11:46,288
At least as a parent.

156
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:04,473
She often talks about
fond memories of Youngsan,

157
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:07,935
so whenever I meet people from there,
I feel at home as well.

158
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:10,354
-She ran away?
-Yes.

159
00:12:10,938 --> 00:12:13,232
She left town as soon as she graduated.

160
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:15,651
She ran away from her crimes.

161
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:30,458
SEOUL TO YOUNGSAN

162
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:41,844
KIM JAE-EUN

163
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,525
You've been living
a happy life, haven't you?

164
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:41,654
NEW MESSAGE FROM SEUNG-HEE

165
00:13:45,866 --> 00:13:47,326
MEDICAL STUDENT COMMITS SUICIDE
AFTER BEING EXPOSED BY NAM

166
00:13:49,828 --> 00:13:51,497
Your husband killed someone as well.

167
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,583
By the way,

168
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,418
does he know about your past?

169
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:12,309
INCOMING CALL

170
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,607
-Hey, Seung-hee.
-I saw the news.

171
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:22,236
Hey.

172
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:23,362
Look, Seung-hee…

173
00:14:23,445 --> 00:14:25,114
Did you think fleeing to Seoul
and changing your name

174
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:28,075
would cover up the murder you committed?

175
00:14:29,243 --> 00:14:32,997
If that's what you wanted,
you should have kept a low profile.

176
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,790
Did you think no one would recognize you

177
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:37,626
when you're the wife of an assemblyman?

178
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:42,006
Come to Youngsan.

179
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,674
We should…

180
00:14:44,592 --> 00:14:46,051
continue our little chat.

181
00:14:48,512 --> 00:14:50,139
Come here tomorrow.

182
00:14:50,806 --> 00:14:52,766
And don't even think about running away.

183
00:14:54,768 --> 00:14:57,021
Seung-hee--

184
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:08,449
YOUR HUSBAND KILLED SOMEONE AS WELL.
DOES HE KNOW ABOUT YOUR PAST?

185
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:23,797
Mom.

186
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:27,551
Mom.

187
00:15:27,635 --> 00:15:29,178
Hey, I'm home.

188
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:33,349
Where have you been all day?

189
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:35,517
Sorry.

190
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,685
I had to take care of something.

191
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,772
Mom.

192
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:43,025
What is it?

193
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,443
Well…

194
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:47,237
I know we're supposed to go
shopping for land tomorrow,

195
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,323
but can you go without me?

196
00:15:50,157 --> 00:15:50,991
Why?

197
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:53,077
Something's come up.

198
00:15:53,994 --> 00:15:56,622
You're meeting your friends
in the evening anyway.

199
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:58,958
I'll go with you next time, okay?

200
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,709
Just for tomorrow.

201
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:03,420
I wouldn't be of much help anyway.

202
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:09,009
Hey, is Ki-young home yet?

203
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:14,181
"Ki-young"?

204
00:16:15,599 --> 00:16:18,644
You come home
after spending the entire day out,

205
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:21,730
and the first person
you ask about is your husband?

206
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:26,694
Are you not worried about me
who's been at home all alone?

207
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:32,324
You two should have just gone
to live in Australia without me.

208
00:16:36,036 --> 00:16:37,037
Mom.

209
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:39,790
Could you please stop saying that?

210
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:43,252
I'm really sorry for saying
I wanted to move to Australia.

211
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:45,504
But I didn't go. So please--

212
00:16:45,587 --> 00:16:46,755
I don't want to hear it.

213
00:16:47,756 --> 00:16:51,176
You're the only child I have left
after Seung-ho passed away,

214
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:55,014
but I don't want to talk
to a heartless person like you anymore.

215
00:16:55,723 --> 00:16:58,017
I'll go by myself tomorrow.

216
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,686
And I'll drop dead right there

217
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:02,354
-and go meet Seung-ho.
-Mom.

218
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:06,900
Fine.

219
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:08,360
I'll come with you, okay?

220
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:10,237
I'm sorry about everything
and I'll come with you.

221
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:12,948
So please just stop it, will you?

222
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,961
COME TO THIS ADDRESS

223
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:34,011
Come to this address at 7 p.m. tomorrow.

224
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:37,681
You murderer.

225
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:49,902
DELETE

226
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:51,695
YOU MURDERER

227
00:17:51,779 --> 00:17:52,988
DELETE FROM THIS DEVICE

228
00:18:14,134 --> 00:18:16,553
I'll revise the parts you mentioned today

229
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:17,846
and report back to you.

230
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:18,972
Yes, that would be great.

231
00:18:20,015 --> 00:18:21,767
But if I'm being honest,

232
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:24,353
It seems a bit premature
to discuss the next term's agenda

233
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:27,022
as we prepare for the upcoming election.

234
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:28,357
Not at all, sir.

235
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:30,567
You should definitely look far ahead.

236
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:34,071
I decided to work with you this term

237
00:18:34,154 --> 00:18:37,157
because I saw you
advocating for the underprivileged

238
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:39,827
during your previous term.

239
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:43,580
I didn't join to be here
for just a single term.

240
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:47,584
You need to stay in politics

241
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:50,003
and improve our country.

242
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:51,088
Absolutely.

243
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:52,673
And don't worry about the election.

244
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:54,258
We'll do all the legwork.

245
00:18:54,341 --> 00:18:56,009
I've been jogging 30 minutes a day.

246
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:58,470
Take it easy.

247
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:01,849
Thank you for your encouragement.

248
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,225
I'll do my best.

249
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:04,476
-You got this, sir!
-You got this.

250
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,118
Why are you out here?

251
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:22,578
Ki-young.

252
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:28,083
Were you waiting for me?

253
00:19:29,751 --> 00:19:32,212
You weren't coming home,
so I thought you left me.

254
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:36,967
Do you want to go out for dinner tonight?

255
00:19:37,634 --> 00:19:38,635
It's been a while.

256
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:40,888
Maybe another time.

257
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:43,056
My mom is home alone.

258
00:19:45,767 --> 00:19:46,643
Ki-young.

259
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:50,647
Things will…

260
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:53,233
get better soon.

261
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:06,371
Hey, come and eat.

262
00:20:06,455 --> 00:20:09,041
Hye-joo isn't eating. She has a headache.

263
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:10,834
Maybe she has a cold.

264
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,170
Are you feeling better?

265
00:20:14,838 --> 00:20:16,632
-Yes.
-Go ahead and eat.

266
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:19,509
I'll eat after bringing her some porridge.

267
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:21,136
I'll bring it to her.

268
00:21:15,148 --> 00:21:16,400
What are you…

269
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:19,528
Give me that.
Why are you touching my phone?

270
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:22,864
MISSED CALL FROM HUSBAND

271
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:29,705
Don't come into my room or touch my stuff
without my permission. Understand?

272
00:21:32,249 --> 00:21:33,250
Okay.

273
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:34,710
I'm sorry.

274
00:22:15,292 --> 00:22:16,626
Hi, honey.

275
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:18,920
I missed your call.

276
00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:21,214
Sorry. What's up?

277
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:23,967
